 # Forge Tree[m
 [m
[31m-[![npm](https://img.shields.io/npm/v/forge-tree.svg)](https://www.npmjs.com/package/forge-tree)[m
[31m-[![npm downloads](https://img.shields.io/npm/dm/forge-tree.svg)](https://www.npmjs.com/package/forge-tree)[m
[31m-[![license](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-MIT-blue.svg)](LICENSE)[m
[32m+[m[32m[![npm version](https://badge.fury.io/js/forge-tree.svg)](https://badge.fury.io/js/forge-tree)[m[41m[m
[32m+[m[32m[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT)[m[41m[m
[32m+[m[32m[![Node.js Version](https://img.shields.io/node/v/forge-tree.svg)](https://nodejs.org)[m[41m[m
 [m
[31m-Interactive CLI to scaffold projects from an **ASCII directory tree**. It parses hierarchies, generates files/folders, creates dotfiles/formatters, and can smart-run tools like `create-next-app`, `firebase init`, or `npm init` where appropriate.[m
[32m+[m[32mA powerful tool to scaffold project structures from ASCII tree diagrams. Supports smart detection of project types, custom templates, and extensive configuration options.[m[41m[m
[32m+[m[41m[m
